# Frontend Architecture Rules

Use Next.js with JavaScript.

Before modifying code:
1. Inspect existing folders and imports.
2. Reuse existing aliases from jsconfig.json.
3. Reuse existing MUI and template conventions.
4. Avoid installing new libraries unless required.
5. Keep implementation incremental.

Recommended folders:
src/components/predictions
src/components/matches
src/components/subscription
src/components/bankroll
src/services
src/lib
src/data/mock

Recommended routes:
- /dashboard
- /matches
- /predictions
- /history
- /bankroll
- /pricing

Component rules:
- Components should be small and readable.
- Do not mix API fetching, formatting and large UI blocks in one file.
- Use shared helpers for formatting confidence, risk and stake.
- Locked premium content should be masked visually, but backend must enforce access.
- Always render loading, empty and error states when integrating real APIs.

Access rules:
- Free users can see 2 full predictions per day.
- Premium users can see all predictions.
- Locked cards may show match name, time, competition and teaser information.
- Locked cards must hide pick, market, stake and rationale.
